import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.hist(data['pressure'], bins=20, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['pressure'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['pressure'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['pressure'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['pressure'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Pressure')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of pressure?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['pressure'], data['temperature'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Pressure')
    ax.set_ylabel('Temperature')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between temperature and pressure?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
